<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="250" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1440,411,868]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,484,508]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from similarly colored congenerics by the broadly explanate elytral margins (
<figureCitation box="[336,409,519,543]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1854,1877]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,629,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-507@4.[151,1436,623,1833]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Dorsal habitus views of Phaenochilus species. 1, P. renipunctus Chapin (holotype, female; TL=3.7 mm); 2, P. mikado Lewis (non-type, male; TL=4.0 mm); 3, P. metasternalis Miyatake (non-type, male; TL=3.4 mm); 4, P. punctifrons Weise (holotype, female; TL=4.0 mm); 5, P.kashaya,n. sp. (holotype, male; TL=3.8 mm) 6, P. ruficollis Weise (paratype of P. celebensis, female; TL=4.8 mm); 7, P. monostigma Weise (non-type from W. Schultze, possibly from the same series as the holotype, disarticulated, sex not determined; TL=4.2 mm)." pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[423,454,519,543]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[397,1195,186,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-58@10.[354,1232,185,1955]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Frontal views of Phaenochilus species, males (for comparative purposes, size adjusted to constant head width using outer margin of eyes as a landmark). 25, P. punctifrons Weise; 26, P. metasternalis Miyatake; 27, P.kashaya, n. sp." pageId="11" pageNumber="250">26</figureCitation>
), the central part of the metasternum densely covered with long hairlike setae (may be lost through abrasion), and the male genitalia which has the basal lobe distinctly undulate on one side and constricted near base (
<figureCitation box="[401,497,591,615]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[155,1435,949,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-416@7.[151,1436,949,1756]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. Male genitalia of Phaenochilus species. 12, P. metasternalis Miyatake: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (reproduced from Miyatake 1970b). 13, P. kashaya, n. sp.: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (holotype). Scale bar applies to figs 12–13." pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Fig. 12a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1440,411,868]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">
A small black leather notebook associated with Chapin’s slide collection (USNM) documents that he performed a whole body dissection of a female of “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chapin" authorityYear="1965" box="[759,916,664,688]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctifrons">
<emphasis box="[759,916,664,688]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">P. punctifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from Java (Java, 
<date box="[1142,1259,663,687]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" value="1911-02">Feb. 1911</date>
, R.L.Woglum). Although we could not find the resulting slide mounted material which he designated “X-15,” the remaining specimens from Java, Buitenzorg (=Bogor), and 
<collectingCountry box="[729,842,735,759]" name="Singapore" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Singapore</collectingCountry>
in the series that Chapin studied all belong to 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miyatake" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metasternalis">P. metasternalis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Ren Shunxiang 
<emphasis box="[505,557,772,796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">et al</emphasis>
. (2009) report the presence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miyatake" authorityYear="1970" box="[924,1106,772,796]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metasternalis">
<emphasis box="[924,1106,772,796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">P. metasternalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Chinese provinces of Yunnan, Anhui, Guangdong, Guangxi, and Hainan. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoang, D. N." box="[730,885,807,832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" pagination="11 - 17" refId="ref10184" refString="Hoang, D. N. (1981) New data on the subfamily Chilocorinae (Coccinellidae, Coleoptera) in Vietnam. Tap chi Sinh Vat Hoc, 3 (1), 11 - 17 (in Vietnamese)." type="journal article" year="1981">Hoang (1981)</bibRefCitation>
reports this species from Trung Quoc, 
<collectingCountry box="[1321,1432,807,831]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Viet Nam</collectingCountry>
. (See also “Remarks” section for 
<taxonomicName box="[517,645,844,868]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis box="[517,645,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">P. ruficollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, below.)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
